1
00:01:44,104 --> 00:01:46,106
(distant male voice)
 Lily...

2
00:01:52,713 --> 00:01:54,982
Where are you, Lily?

3
00:02:26,447 --> 00:02:28,482
Lily!

4
00:02:36,089 --> 00:02:38,592
Where are you?

5
00:02:54,708 --> 00:02:57,911
[bell rings]

6
00:03:08,456 --> 00:03:10,057
Lily!

7
00:03:43,023 --> 00:03:46,294
Lily...

8
00:03:46,327 --> 00:03:48,929
Where are you, Lily?

9
00:03:51,532 --> 00:03:53,667
Lily...

10
00:04:01,141 --> 00:04:02,643
Lily!

11
00:04:08,616 --> 00:04:10,451
I'm coming,
Grandma!

12
00:04:16,724 --> 00:04:18,592
Come on, Joey.

13
00:04:21,929 --> 00:04:23,931
I've been callin' and callin'.

14
00:04:23,964 --> 00:04:26,066
Ooh, look at you!

15
00:04:26,099 --> 00:04:28,869
You are filthy!
And no shoes?

16
00:04:28,902 --> 00:04:30,237
Where's your brains?

17
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:33,341
Your Granddad killed
a four-foot rattler

18
00:04:33,374 --> 00:04:35,309
down there only last week.

19
00:04:35,343 --> 00:04:36,243
Really?

20
00:04:37,244 --> 00:04:38,746
Yeah. Watch your feet
on these thorns here.

21
00:04:38,779 --> 00:04:43,283
And you know, there's water
moccasins down there, too.

22
00:04:43,317 --> 00:04:46,253
You gotta listen
to me Lily...

23
00:04:46,286 --> 00:04:47,888
You do.

24
00:04:49,757 --> 00:04:52,259
You could at least wear shoes.

25
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:14,448
Hey, Grandpa.

26
00:05:14,482 --> 00:05:16,116
What'd ya get me today?

27
00:05:16,149 --> 00:05:17,818
Hey, Sunshine.

28
00:05:17,851 --> 00:05:19,687
Where's Grandpa's hug?

29
00:05:22,089 --> 00:05:24,925
Is it M & M's?

30
00:05:24,958 --> 00:05:27,094
Nothin.
I didn't get you nothin'.

31
00:05:27,127 --> 00:05:29,730
Grandpa, what did you get?

32
00:05:29,763 --> 00:05:31,064
Please tell me?

33
00:05:32,332 --> 00:05:34,502
- Edna.
- Hey.

34
00:05:37,471 --> 00:05:40,808
Not until after
you've cleaned up.

35
00:05:40,841 --> 00:05:42,476
Now, hurry, the food's ready.

36
00:05:42,510 --> 00:05:44,645
Oh, Grandpa,
you're kidding with me.

37
00:05:44,678 --> 00:05:46,680
I know you got me something.

38
00:05:46,714 --> 00:05:48,916
Come on.

39
00:05:53,454 --> 00:05:55,155
Thanks!

40
00:05:56,023 --> 00:05:58,325
Lily, not until after supper.
You hear me?

41
00:05:58,358 --> 00:06:00,761
I want you to wash up so you
can help Grandma set the table.

42
00:06:00,794 --> 00:06:03,363
Thomas, not till
after you clean up.

43
00:06:03,397 --> 00:06:05,298
You got to set an example.

44
00:06:05,332 --> 00:06:07,601
All right, all right.
I'm goin'.

45
00:06:08,736 --> 00:06:15,375
* It's cold tonight 
 down by the river *

46
00:06:15,409 --> 00:06:22,450
* The wind is whistlin' 
 thru the pines *

47
00:06:22,483 --> 00:06:30,157
* We walked here 
 so many times together *

48
00:06:30,190 --> 00:06:35,829
* I can almost feel 
 your hand in mine *

49
00:06:44,605 --> 00:06:46,373
Guess what I built today?

50
00:06:46,406 --> 00:06:47,808
What did you do?

51
00:06:47,841 --> 00:06:50,410
I built a carpet room
made of moss.

52
00:06:50,444 --> 00:06:51,579
You did?

53
00:06:51,612 --> 00:06:52,913
Mmm hmm.

54
00:06:52,946 --> 00:06:55,115
And it felt so good
under my feet.

55
00:06:55,148 --> 00:06:59,186
Then, I fell asleep...

56
00:06:59,219 --> 00:07:01,789
And I had that dream again,
you know,

57
00:07:01,822 --> 00:07:03,891
the one about the ocean?

58
00:07:03,924 --> 00:07:05,559
Mmm hmm.

59
00:07:05,593 --> 00:07:07,394
I always wake up
before I see it.

60
00:07:07,427 --> 00:07:10,263
- You do?
- Mmm hmm.

61
00:07:10,297 --> 00:07:13,967
Then I hear that voice
calling my name.

62
00:07:14,001 --> 00:07:17,304
Do you think it was
Daddy's voice?

63
00:07:17,337 --> 00:07:20,440
Well, what do you think?

64
00:07:20,474 --> 00:07:23,410
I know it was him -
it had to be.

65
00:07:24,978 --> 00:07:27,114
Tell me about the ocean?

66
00:07:27,147 --> 00:07:31,819
Lily, Grandma tells you
this story every single day.

67
00:07:31,852 --> 00:07:33,386
Don't you ever get tired of it?

68
00:07:33,420 --> 00:07:35,222
I know, but I want
to hear it again.

69
00:07:35,255 --> 00:07:36,990
All right, well...
When your daddy was--

70
00:07:37,024 --> 00:07:38,959
Hey!

71
00:07:39,459 --> 00:07:41,529
Hi, sweetie.

72
00:07:41,562 --> 00:07:43,463
How's my little girl?

73
00:07:43,497 --> 00:07:44,698
Good.

74
00:07:44,732 --> 00:07:46,199
Did you have any good
adventures today?

75
00:07:46,233 --> 00:07:47,901
Yes?

76
00:07:47,935 --> 00:07:50,871
Oh!
Not before dinner.

77
00:07:53,674 --> 00:07:58,278
Edna...Thomas is spoiling her.

78
00:07:58,311 --> 00:07:59,446
No, he isn't.

79
00:07:59,479 --> 00:08:01,782
It's just a 'weeee'
little bit of candy.

80
00:08:26,173 --> 00:08:28,041
Hello, everybody.

81
00:08:29,309 --> 00:08:31,912
Big day!
Big, big day!

82
00:08:39,987 --> 00:08:42,322
Mmmm, I'm starvin'.

83
00:08:42,355 --> 00:08:43,757
Smells good.

84
00:08:43,791 --> 00:08:45,458
It is good.

85
00:08:46,860 --> 00:08:48,629
Lily, why don't you
come over here

86
00:08:48,662 --> 00:08:51,064
and give your soon-to-be
Daddy a big kiss?

87
00:08:51,098 --> 00:08:53,233
You're not my Daddy yet.

88
00:08:53,266 --> 00:08:55,268
He will be, Lily.

89
00:08:55,302 --> 00:08:57,237
Don't be ugly.

90
00:08:58,405 --> 00:09:01,174
Sweetheart...

91
00:09:01,208 --> 00:09:04,544
Dean just wants to be
a good Daddy to ya.

92
00:09:04,578 --> 00:09:06,847
Okay?
That's all.

93
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:09,583
Now you go apologize.

94
00:09:11,384 --> 00:09:13,621
I'm sorry.

95
00:09:13,654 --> 00:09:16,189
Well, now,
that's okay, Pumpkin.

96
00:09:16,223 --> 00:09:18,158
You'll get used to me,

97
00:09:18,191 --> 00:09:21,695
then we'll all be just
one big happy family.

98
00:09:21,729 --> 00:09:22,996
Yeah, I hope so.

99
00:09:31,371 --> 00:09:32,840
Thank you.

100
00:09:32,873 --> 00:09:34,374
You're welcome.

101
00:09:36,644 --> 00:09:38,545
Oh, the blessing thing.

102
00:09:43,651 --> 00:09:45,252
Dear Lord,

103
00:09:45,285 --> 00:09:47,755
Bless this food
we are about to receive.

104
00:09:47,788 --> 00:09:50,590
Thank you for the blessings that
you have bestowed upon us.

105
00:09:50,624 --> 00:09:51,792
Amen.

106
00:09:51,825 --> 00:09:53,326
Amen.

107
00:10:00,934 --> 00:10:02,402
Ah, ah, Lily.

108
00:10:02,435 --> 00:10:05,205
Just take what you're
gonna eat, Pumpkin.

109
00:10:10,377 --> 00:10:12,846
Did y'all hear
about Copeland Franks?

110
00:10:12,880 --> 00:10:16,516
He spotted that panther,
over there near his cabin.

111
00:10:16,549 --> 00:10:17,818
That stupid Indian.

112
00:10:17,851 --> 00:10:19,419
Why don't he just
kill the damn thing?

113
00:10:19,452 --> 00:10:21,021
That's just like an Indian.

114
00:10:21,054 --> 00:10:23,423
Dean, they'll be no cursin'
at my dinner table.

115
00:10:23,456 --> 00:10:27,360
Sorry, Thomas.
I just can't stand Indians.

116
00:10:27,394 --> 00:10:29,697
And as for Copeland Franks -

117
00:10:29,730 --> 00:10:31,631
he's one of the best
trackers I've ever seen.

118
00:10:31,665 --> 00:10:34,267
He is also one of my closest
and dearest friends.

119
00:10:34,301 --> 00:10:35,869
Okay, but--

120
00:10:35,903 --> 00:10:38,171
Grandpa, guess what I built.

121
00:10:38,205 --> 00:10:40,373
Well, let me guess.

122
00:10:40,407 --> 00:10:43,777
Umm, I bet you built a boat.

123
00:10:43,811 --> 00:10:45,478
We need a new boat.

124
00:10:45,512 --> 00:10:47,380
No, Grandpa.

125
00:10:47,414 --> 00:10:49,983
I didn't build a boat.
I made a carpet room.

126
00:10:50,017 --> 00:10:52,119
I put moss all over the ground.

127
00:10:52,152 --> 00:10:55,355
It took me all day,
and I did it down by the creek.

128
00:10:55,388 --> 00:10:56,556
Down by the creek!

129
00:10:56,589 --> 00:10:58,258
Lily, how many times
do you have to be told?

130
00:10:58,291 --> 00:11:01,762
There are snakes down there -
and not to mention that panther.

131
00:11:01,795 --> 00:11:03,864
I haven't seen a snake yet!

132
00:11:03,897 --> 00:11:06,666
And Joey, he won't let
that old panther get me.

133
00:11:06,700 --> 00:11:08,201
Will you, Joey?

134
00:11:08,235 --> 00:11:10,503
Edna, why do you let her go down
to that creek all by herself?

135
00:11:10,537 --> 00:11:12,339
I can't be watching her
every minute.

136
00:11:12,372 --> 00:11:14,407
And you know she
knows those woods,

137
00:11:14,441 --> 00:11:15,909
and she swims like a fish.

138
00:11:15,943 --> 00:11:18,011
And Joey isn't going to let
anything happen to her.

139
00:11:18,045 --> 00:11:19,379
I know.
I'm sorry, Edna.

140
00:11:19,412 --> 00:11:20,981
It's just...

141
00:11:21,014 --> 00:11:23,016
I could not stand it
if something happened to her.

142
00:11:23,050 --> 00:11:25,118
Momma, I'm OK.

143
00:11:26,319 --> 00:11:28,555
Hey, is Donna coming tomorrow?

144
00:11:28,588 --> 00:11:30,023
Yeah.
She and Betty

145
00:11:30,057 --> 00:11:32,425
are gonna come
and get some good canning goods.

146
00:11:32,459 --> 00:11:34,661
She's gonna get some
peaches, okra.

147
00:11:34,694 --> 00:11:36,463
She and Donna
gonna be here

148
00:11:36,496 --> 00:11:38,498
first thing in the morning,
bright and early.

149
00:11:38,531 --> 00:11:41,068
I cannot believe I have
to work tomorrow.

150
00:11:41,101 --> 00:11:43,536
You can sell a lot
of cars on the weekend.

151
00:11:43,570 --> 00:11:47,307
I know, but I am supposed to be
planning the wedding reception.

152
00:11:47,340 --> 00:11:50,010
Baby, it can't happen
soon enough for me.

153
00:11:50,043 --> 00:11:52,479
I say we run off
and get married tonight.

154
00:11:52,512 --> 00:11:55,115
What do we need all
this other stuff for?

155
00:11:55,148 --> 00:12:00,620
Because I want to have a church
weddin' with all the trimmin's -

156
00:12:00,653 --> 00:12:03,791
and I want Lily to be there.

157
00:12:03,824 --> 00:12:05,692
I can't wait to see Donna.

158
00:12:05,725 --> 00:12:08,695
I haven't had anyone
to play with in so long.

159
00:12:09,863 --> 00:12:13,400
Grandpa, do you believe that
the creek flows to the ocean?

160
00:12:13,433 --> 00:12:15,602
Yeah, it could.

161
00:12:15,635 --> 00:12:19,072
Take the creek a few
miles down to the river.

162
00:12:19,106 --> 00:12:21,508
I reckon it'd take about a week.
Why?

163
00:12:21,541 --> 00:12:23,376
I want to go there so bad.

164
00:12:23,410 --> 00:12:26,880
If I close my eyes I can hear
the sounds of the waves,

165
00:12:26,914 --> 00:12:29,149
and the seagulls.

166
00:12:29,182 --> 00:12:31,051
I can almost smell it.

167
00:12:31,084 --> 00:12:33,120
Does it smell fishy?

168
00:13:00,480 --> 00:13:03,616
Joey, what do you think
it's like at the ocean?

169
00:13:04,751 --> 00:13:06,586
Do you think that Daddy
will know I'm there?

170
00:13:08,488 --> 00:13:10,423
We'll go there someday.

171
00:13:10,457 --> 00:13:13,360
Just you, me and Andrew.

172
00:13:13,393 --> 00:13:17,430
Momma can go too, if she can
get some time off work.

173
00:13:17,464 --> 00:13:19,632
And I don't want her
to bring you-know-who.

174
00:13:21,734 --> 00:13:23,170
Hi, baby.

175
00:13:23,203 --> 00:13:24,471
Hey, Momma.

176
00:13:24,504 --> 00:13:26,039
Here, let me wash your back.

177
00:13:26,073 --> 00:13:28,508
No. I can do it myself.

178
00:13:28,541 --> 00:13:30,310
Oooh...

179
00:13:30,343 --> 00:13:33,413
Gettin' too old for your
Momma to baby you, huh?

180
00:13:33,446 --> 00:13:38,085
Honey, it scares me how
fast you are growing up.

181
00:13:38,118 --> 00:13:39,719
Yep.

182
00:13:39,752 --> 00:13:41,388
I'll be grown up
before you know it.

183
00:13:41,421 --> 00:13:44,457
Yeah, but you're always
gonna be my baby girl.

184
00:13:46,093 --> 00:13:50,697
Now why don't you get out
before you turn into a prune.

185
00:13:50,730 --> 00:13:52,465
Okay.

186
00:13:52,499 --> 00:13:54,434
Okay.

187
00:14:08,448 --> 00:14:11,985
[humming "My Bonnie 
 Lies Over the Ocean"]

188
00:14:24,531 --> 00:14:25,832
Guess what, Andrew?

189
00:14:25,865 --> 00:14:27,334
We're going to
the ocean someday.

190
00:14:27,367 --> 00:14:29,036
Won't that be fun?

191
00:14:31,238 --> 00:14:33,573
And I can be
closer to Daddy.

192
00:14:39,046 --> 00:14:40,780
Good night, Andrew.

193
00:14:40,813 --> 00:14:44,817
Hey, Joey, we can show
Donna the carpet room.

194
00:14:49,957 --> 00:14:52,459
Do you think I'm stupid?

195
00:14:52,492 --> 00:14:54,594
Hmm?

196
00:14:54,627 --> 00:14:56,563
Do ya?

197
00:14:58,966 --> 00:15:00,900
No, sir.

198
00:15:08,175 --> 00:15:11,244
I know one thing.

199
00:15:11,278 --> 00:15:15,748
You lied to me
about that dog.

200
00:15:18,651 --> 00:15:22,222
What did I say was gonna
happen if you lied to me?

201
00:15:22,255 --> 00:15:24,124
Hmm?
What did I say?

202
00:15:26,026 --> 00:15:28,295
I was gonna get a whippin'.

203
00:15:29,229 --> 00:15:31,398
You were gonna
get a whoopin'.

204
00:15:32,165 --> 00:15:35,268
Now, let me ask you.
Did you lie to me?

205
00:15:35,302 --> 00:15:39,372
- Did ya?
- Yes.

206
00:15:39,406 --> 00:15:41,008
You did?

207
00:15:43,010 --> 00:15:45,045
Well...

208
00:15:45,078 --> 00:15:47,680
then we're gonna have
to give you that whoopin'.

209
00:15:50,283 --> 00:15:54,654
I hate to have
to do this, Lily.

210
00:15:54,687 --> 00:15:57,490
It's for your own good.

211
00:16:06,699 --> 00:16:10,370
These are critical years
in a young lady's life.

212
00:16:14,707 --> 00:16:22,015
Now...I saw you feed
that dog under the table.

213
00:16:22,049 --> 00:16:25,152
And if I ever see that again,

214
00:16:25,185 --> 00:16:27,287
the dog is gone.

215
00:16:27,320 --> 00:16:29,389
Do you hear me?

216
00:16:29,422 --> 00:16:31,424
That dog is dead!

217
00:16:32,359 --> 00:16:34,494
You hear me now?

218
00:16:34,527 --> 00:16:36,763
- I'm sorry.
- You're sorry?

219
00:16:38,498 --> 00:16:40,367
Did you hear what I said?

220
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:41,868
Do you hear me?

221
00:16:43,170 --> 00:16:44,871
Do you hear me?

222
00:16:44,904 --> 00:16:46,139
Yes.

223
00:16:46,173 --> 00:16:47,440
Yes?

224
00:16:47,474 --> 00:16:48,875
Yes.

225
00:16:48,908 --> 00:16:49,942
Yes, what?

226
00:16:49,976 --> 00:16:51,311
Yes, Daddy.

227
00:16:53,046 --> 00:16:55,048
Yes, Daddy.

228
00:16:56,316 --> 00:16:59,119
That's better.

229
00:17:03,123 --> 00:17:05,125
Now...

230
00:17:10,163 --> 00:17:11,798
Get down.

231
00:17:14,301 --> 00:17:16,069
Get down.

232
00:17:17,070 --> 00:17:18,971
[belt cracking]

233
00:17:36,156 --> 00:17:39,058
And if you mention
this to anybody,

234
00:17:39,092 --> 00:17:41,494
well...

235
00:17:42,795 --> 00:17:45,732
Daddy loves you, Pumpkin.

236
00:18:33,646 --> 00:18:38,351
*

237
00:19:09,882 --> 00:19:13,353
Now, what kind
of tree is that?

238
00:19:14,954 --> 00:19:16,523
Lily?

239
00:19:16,556 --> 00:19:17,990
Lily, are you listenin'?

240
00:19:18,024 --> 00:19:19,959
Sorry, Grandpa.

241
00:19:19,992 --> 00:19:21,494
That's an oak.

242
00:19:21,528 --> 00:19:23,296
That's good, that's good.

243
00:19:23,330 --> 00:19:25,265
How 'bout
that one over there?

244
00:19:25,298 --> 00:19:27,400
Maple?

245
00:19:27,434 --> 00:19:29,336
All right, smarty pants.

246
00:19:29,369 --> 00:19:32,405
What kind of bird is that
circlin' up there?

247
00:19:32,439 --> 00:19:34,207
Hawk.

248
00:19:34,241 --> 00:19:36,509
Boy, you're gettin'
faster and faster.

249
00:19:36,543 --> 00:19:38,578
Pretty soon you're gonna
be quicker than me.

250
00:19:38,611 --> 00:19:40,613
I won't have anything
left to teach you.

251
00:19:41,448 --> 00:19:43,283
What's the news
on that panther?

252
00:19:43,316 --> 00:19:45,418
I heard her this morning.
She sounded real close.

253
00:19:45,452 --> 00:19:47,119
Yeah, she is.

254
00:19:47,153 --> 00:19:49,656
Them poachers been trappin'
out her food supply.

255
00:19:49,689 --> 00:19:51,824
She'll be going after the
livestock pretty soon -

256
00:19:51,858 --> 00:19:54,227
or even worse.

257
00:19:54,261 --> 00:19:57,497
Hey, lookie there.
Ya'll made fire.

258
00:19:57,530 --> 00:19:59,232
Hey, Lily, what do
ya say we ask

259
00:19:59,266 --> 00:20:02,168
Copeland to give us
our new lesson for the day.

260
00:20:02,201 --> 00:20:04,971
We were about to learn how
to tell time from the sun.

261
00:20:05,004 --> 00:20:06,873
Will you be
our teacher today?

262
00:20:06,906 --> 00:20:08,508
I'd be proud to.

263
00:20:08,541 --> 00:20:10,977
Now you lower your arm,

264
00:20:11,010 --> 00:20:15,047
until it's just level
with the horizon.

265
00:20:15,081 --> 00:20:17,049
Now, what time is it?

266
00:20:17,083 --> 00:20:18,551
Six a.m.

267
00:20:18,585 --> 00:20:21,187
- I believe you've got it.
- Grandpa, I got it.

268
00:20:21,220 --> 00:20:23,723
Hey, I knew you
could do that.

269
00:20:23,756 --> 00:20:26,326
Lily, I want to give
you something.

270
00:20:26,359 --> 00:20:28,961
I've had it since
I was your age.

271
00:20:28,995 --> 00:20:30,830
My Grandpa gave it to me.

272
00:20:30,863 --> 00:20:32,432
It's a compass.

273
00:20:32,465 --> 00:20:36,068
You can find your way
no matter where you are.

274
00:20:36,102 --> 00:20:39,672
Of course, you know what to do
if you're lost and you lose it?

275
00:20:39,706 --> 00:20:41,474
I do.

276
00:20:41,508 --> 00:20:44,010
The moss grows on the
north side of the tree.

277
00:20:44,043 --> 00:20:46,546
The sun rises in the east,

278
00:20:46,579 --> 00:20:49,015
and it sets in the west.

279
00:20:49,048 --> 00:20:52,652
And I can always locate
the North Star at night.

280
00:20:54,887 --> 00:20:56,723
I'll never lose it.

281
00:20:59,392 --> 00:21:00,893
Now, come on -
let's see if we

282
00:21:00,927 --> 00:21:02,895
remember what y'all
just learned.

283
00:21:05,264 --> 00:21:07,334
Hands to the center
of the sky.

284
00:21:07,367 --> 00:21:09,235
Now lower your arm...

285
00:21:09,268 --> 00:21:11,938
level with the horizon.

286
00:21:25,652 --> 00:21:28,988
Ooh, look at you!

287
00:21:29,021 --> 00:21:31,324
I haven't seen you in weeks.

288
00:21:31,358 --> 00:21:33,393
And look how big
you've gotten!

289
00:21:33,426 --> 00:21:36,363
I've grown a lot, Grandma.
Where's Lily?

290
00:21:37,897 --> 00:21:40,166
Well, now she's
off with Grandpa

291
00:21:40,199 --> 00:21:42,402
on their Saturday adventure.

292
00:21:42,435 --> 00:21:44,371
Probably down there in the
woods, which you know

293
00:21:44,404 --> 00:21:46,238
is no place for a little girl.

294
00:21:46,272 --> 00:21:47,874
But you know how
much she loves it.

295
00:21:47,907 --> 00:21:49,442
She can't wait to see you.

296
00:21:49,476 --> 00:21:50,743
I'm gonna call her.

297
00:21:50,777 --> 00:21:51,978
Lily!

298
00:21:52,011 --> 00:21:53,613
Thomas!

299
00:21:53,646 --> 00:21:55,482
Company!

300
00:21:55,515 --> 00:21:57,584
I brought those
jars for canning.

301
00:21:57,617 --> 00:21:58,918
Good.

302
00:21:58,951 --> 00:22:00,720
I got some more
goodies for ya.

303
00:22:00,753 --> 00:22:02,922
And I got a nice cold
pitcher of sweet tea

304
00:22:02,955 --> 00:22:05,057
waiting for you,
and a hot apple pie

305
00:22:05,091 --> 00:22:07,427
right out of the oven
for you, missy.

306
00:22:07,460 --> 00:22:09,662
Oh, there goes my helper.

307
00:22:09,696 --> 00:22:12,298
Hi, Lily.
How are you?

308
00:22:19,372 --> 00:22:22,041
Hey, Thomas, look who's here.

309
00:22:22,074 --> 00:22:23,576
Hi.

310
00:22:23,610 --> 00:22:25,912
Good to see ya, girl.

311
00:22:25,945 --> 00:22:28,180
You're just in time
for planting.

312
00:22:28,214 --> 00:22:30,049
Oh, he's puttin' me
to work already.

313
00:22:30,082 --> 00:22:31,784
Oh, Thomas, behave
yourself now, honey.

314
00:22:31,818 --> 00:22:33,786
She just got here.

315
00:22:34,754 --> 00:22:36,889
Ms. McClain said
tell y'all both hi.

316
00:22:36,923 --> 00:22:39,492
Oh, Ms. McClain, she has
a crush on your Daddy.

317
00:22:39,526 --> 00:22:41,327
Oh, no...

318
00:22:46,198 --> 00:22:49,101
Do you know what
Grandpa told me?

319
00:22:49,135 --> 00:22:50,369
No. What?

320
00:22:50,403 --> 00:22:51,971
He says that if I
follow the creek

321
00:22:52,004 --> 00:22:53,573
that I can
get to the ocean.

322
00:22:53,606 --> 00:22:55,408
Do you believe that?

323
00:22:55,442 --> 00:22:56,843
That's hard to believe.

324
00:22:56,876 --> 00:22:58,611
How long would it take
you to get there?

325
00:22:58,645 --> 00:23:01,648
I don't know for sure.
Maybe a week or so.

326
00:23:01,681 --> 00:23:03,450
But I know I'm going.

327
00:23:04,884 --> 00:23:06,753
Oh, Lily, what happened?!

328
00:23:06,786 --> 00:23:09,055
Nothing.
I fell.

329
00:23:09,088 --> 00:23:11,190
How did you fall?
That looks awful.

330
00:23:11,223 --> 00:23:12,859
Does it hurt?

331
00:23:12,892 --> 00:23:14,093
It's okay, really.

332
00:23:14,126 --> 00:23:16,996
Please don't tell Momma.
I wouldn't want her to worry.

333
00:23:17,029 --> 00:23:19,899
And besides, she wouldn't let
me come to the creek anymore.

334
00:23:19,932 --> 00:23:21,568
Why don't you tell my Momma?

335
00:23:21,601 --> 00:23:25,104
She could help make them better.
You need medicine.

336
00:23:25,137 --> 00:23:26,639
Promise!

337
00:23:27,874 --> 00:23:30,710
Okay, I promise.

338
00:23:39,819 --> 00:23:45,658
Grandpa, about the ocean -
have you ever seen it?

339
00:23:45,692 --> 00:23:47,994
I have.

340
00:23:48,027 --> 00:23:51,030
Is it beautiful
and peaceful there?

341
00:23:51,063 --> 00:23:53,099
It's beautiful.
It's probably one of

342
00:23:53,132 --> 00:23:55,401
the prettiest places
I've ever seen.

343
00:23:55,434 --> 00:23:57,737
Maybe we'll take
you there someday.

344
00:23:59,939 --> 00:24:02,875
About Daddy...

345
00:24:05,645 --> 00:24:08,214
Do you think
he'll ever come back?

346
00:24:08,247 --> 00:24:12,118
I mean...he got lost
at sea, right?

347
00:24:12,151 --> 00:24:14,587
And I know he was one of

348
00:24:14,621 --> 00:24:16,623
the best sailors
in the United States Navy.

349
00:24:16,656 --> 00:24:18,925
Lily, your Daddy -
he loved the ocean.

350
00:24:18,958 --> 00:24:21,327
He knew all his life
what he wanted to do.

351
00:24:21,360 --> 00:24:23,763
He was happy being a sailor.

352
00:24:23,796 --> 00:24:26,265
I wish we can go today.

353
00:24:26,298 --> 00:24:27,634
I'd never feel hurt...

354
00:24:27,667 --> 00:24:29,636
or afraid of anything.

355
00:24:29,669 --> 00:24:32,238
Lily.
Lily!

356
00:25:59,458 --> 00:26:01,360
What you doin', baby?

357
00:26:04,396 --> 00:26:07,700
He was really handsome.

358
00:26:07,734 --> 00:26:10,236
Yeah.

359
00:26:10,269 --> 00:26:14,240
You remind me
so much of him.

360
00:26:14,273 --> 00:26:18,444
He loved the outdoors, too.

361
00:26:18,477 --> 00:26:20,913
He couldn't kill a thing.

362
00:26:20,947 --> 00:26:24,951
Never was a hunter...

363
00:26:24,984 --> 00:26:28,287
but he was
a sailor though.

364
00:26:30,823 --> 00:26:34,126
He would be
so proud of you.

365
00:26:35,561 --> 00:26:37,764
Do you still miss him?

366
00:26:37,797 --> 00:26:40,199
Yes.

367
00:26:40,232 --> 00:26:44,871
And I will always miss him.

368
00:26:44,904 --> 00:26:49,341
I loved him more than
anyone ever knew.

369
00:26:52,812 --> 00:26:55,014
He could make me laugh

370
00:26:55,047 --> 00:26:57,917
at the smallest,
silliest things.

371
00:27:03,890 --> 00:27:08,594
But...I have Dean now.

372
00:27:10,697 --> 00:27:13,700
Honey, he just wants to
be a good Daddy to you.

373
00:27:13,733 --> 00:27:15,001
That's my Daddy.

374
00:27:15,034 --> 00:27:15,067
That's my only Daddy ever.

375
00:27:17,536 --> 00:27:19,706
Come here, sit up.

376
00:27:24,576 --> 00:27:27,079
Baby...

377
00:27:27,113 --> 00:27:31,017
Dean is not trying
to replace William.

378
00:27:31,050 --> 00:27:32,318
Okay?

379
00:27:32,351 --> 00:27:36,422
No one can replace William.

380
00:27:36,455 --> 00:27:39,759
No one can replace him
in my heart either.

381
00:27:41,260 --> 00:27:43,830
Just don't make me
call him Daddy.

382
00:27:50,669 --> 00:27:53,940
Tom and Edna,
good night.

383
00:27:53,973 --> 00:27:57,076
Now you drive careful,
you hear?

384
00:27:57,109 --> 00:27:58,544
I will.

385
00:27:58,577 --> 00:28:00,112
Mr. Strickland,
good night.

386
00:28:00,146 --> 00:28:01,848
Good night, Dean.

387
00:28:02,114 --> 00:28:04,216
Jenny, you hurry back in.

388
00:28:04,250 --> 00:28:08,755
Thomas, I'm not a little girl.
I know what I am doing.

389
00:28:08,788 --> 00:28:10,222
I know.

390
00:28:10,256 --> 00:28:12,424
But you'll always be
like a daughter to me.

391
00:28:12,458 --> 00:28:14,393
I just want you
to be careful.

392
00:28:19,031 --> 00:28:21,133
Come on, Dad.

393
00:28:35,014 --> 00:28:36,515
Dean.

394
00:28:37,449 --> 00:28:38,717
Dean.

395
00:28:40,219 --> 00:28:42,388
Oh, what happened?

396
00:28:49,996 --> 00:28:52,899
When I look
into your eyes...

397
00:28:55,868 --> 00:28:57,870
Never mind.

398
00:29:22,461 --> 00:29:24,196
Mmm, that's mine.

399
00:29:28,968 --> 00:29:31,103
I have to go.

400
00:29:31,137 --> 00:29:32,872
I have to go, too.

401
00:30:29,695 --> 00:30:33,165
Not much longer.

402
00:30:33,199 --> 00:30:35,968
I can't wait much longer.

403
00:31:35,161 --> 00:31:37,329
Where are you, Lily?

404
00:32:26,012 --> 00:32:28,280
* Is she lonesome now? *

405
00:32:28,314 --> 00:32:30,716
* Is she all alone? *

406
00:32:30,749 --> 00:32:36,088
* I wonder where 
 that good gal's gone *

407
00:32:36,122 --> 00:32:38,090
* Hear the whistle blow *

408
00:32:38,124 --> 00:32:40,526
* Hear the tracks moan *

409
00:32:40,559 --> 00:32:45,397
* I hear that train 
 comin' home *

410
00:32:45,431 --> 00:32:48,134
* Lonesome is the name *

411
00:32:48,167 --> 00:32:50,469
* Of the northbound train *

412
00:32:50,502 --> 00:32:55,541
* The hills are green 
 where she's gone *

413
00:32:55,574 --> 00:32:57,476
* She made up her mind *

414
00:32:57,509 --> 00:33:00,646
* To leave sorrow behind *

415
00:33:00,679 --> 00:33:05,084
* On her way back home *

416
00:33:05,117 --> 00:33:09,321
* There is a place *

417
00:33:09,355 --> 00:33:16,895
* Where her shining face 
 still smiles *

418
00:33:34,813 --> 00:33:37,249
* Does she sing 
 a glad song *

419
00:33:37,283 --> 00:33:39,685
* Or is she sad I'm gone? *

420
00:33:39,718 --> 00:33:44,623
* I hear her voice 
 laugh in a dream *

421
00:33:44,656 --> 00:33:47,593
* How near she seemed *

422
00:33:47,626 --> 00:33:54,700
* When she whispered 
 her sad farewell *

423
00:34:22,761 --> 00:34:27,399
You know, Joey, it's not far
'til we make it to the river.

424
00:34:27,433 --> 00:34:31,203
We'll be there in no time.

425
00:34:34,473 --> 00:34:40,479
My Bonnie lies over the ocean

426
00:34:40,512 --> 00:34:45,951
My Bonnie lies over the sea

427
00:34:45,984 --> 00:34:50,989
My Bonnie lies over the ocean

428
00:34:51,022 --> 00:34:54,960
Bring my Bonnie back to me

429
00:35:17,249 --> 00:35:20,586
My Bonnie lies over the ocean

430
00:35:20,619 --> 00:35:24,190
My Bonnie lies over the sea

431
00:35:24,223 --> 00:35:28,227
My Bonnie lies over the ocean

432
00:35:28,260 --> 00:35:32,231
So bring back
my Bonnie to me

433
00:35:32,264 --> 00:35:36,134
To me, to me...

434
00:35:37,603 --> 00:35:41,673
Did I hear some sweet bird
singin' in the mornin' light?

435
00:35:42,341 --> 00:35:45,777
Oh, he's a charmer.

436
00:35:46,645 --> 00:35:48,547
Always smells good
in this kitchen.

437
00:35:48,580 --> 00:35:49,848
Sure does.

438
00:35:49,881 --> 00:35:51,917
How did you
sleep last night?

439
00:35:51,950 --> 00:35:55,654
That's all I get is
one little peck on the cheek?

440
00:35:57,923 --> 00:36:00,892
I sure did miss
my baby last night.

441
00:36:00,926 --> 00:36:02,728
I missed you, too.

442
00:36:02,761 --> 00:36:04,896
I missed you bad.

443
00:36:06,765 --> 00:36:08,334
Thomas!
Lily!

444
00:36:08,367 --> 00:36:09,935
Breakfast!

445
00:36:09,968 --> 00:36:11,470
Y'all sit down now.

446
00:36:11,503 --> 00:36:12,671
Yes, ma'am.

447
00:36:12,704 --> 00:36:14,873
We got orange juice,
or you can have tomato juice.

448
00:36:14,906 --> 00:36:16,208
Uh, orange, please.

449
00:36:16,242 --> 00:36:17,376
Okay.

450
00:36:17,409 --> 00:36:19,077
- Orange?
- Yes.

451
00:36:19,110 --> 00:36:21,847
Well, you're already back?
I thought you just left.

452
00:36:21,880 --> 00:36:24,283
Thomas, where's Lily?

453
00:36:24,316 --> 00:36:26,117
Uh, I didn't see
her this morning.

454
00:36:26,151 --> 00:36:28,086
I figured she was
sleepin' in.

455
00:36:28,119 --> 00:36:31,457
Well...
Okay.

456
00:36:34,059 --> 00:36:37,396
Lily!
Get down here this instant!

457
00:36:37,429 --> 00:36:39,698
She is probably down there
by that creek again.

458
00:36:39,731 --> 00:36:41,700
I'll go get her.

459
00:36:43,235 --> 00:36:45,237
I'll go get her.

460
00:36:50,041 --> 00:36:54,045
I got some uh, eggs -
cheese in 'em for you.

461
00:36:54,079 --> 00:36:55,113
Thank you.

462
00:36:55,146 --> 00:36:57,716
I do not know what
it is gonna take.

463
00:36:57,749 --> 00:37:00,952
She just won't
mind me anymore.

464
00:37:00,986 --> 00:37:03,088
I'm tellin' ya.
You gotta be stern with her.

465
00:37:03,121 --> 00:37:06,057
All she needs is some good
old-fashioned discipline.

466
00:37:06,091 --> 00:37:08,193
That's the way
my dad handled it.

467
00:37:08,226 --> 00:37:10,095
We all knew better.

468
00:37:10,596 --> 00:37:13,799
God, he used to
beat us silly.

469
00:37:13,832 --> 00:37:16,368
And if we kept at it, things
started disappearing...

470
00:37:16,402 --> 00:37:18,570
our toys, our pets.

471
00:37:18,604 --> 00:37:22,608
My dog, one morning - gone.

472
00:37:22,641 --> 00:37:24,910
What do you mean,
disappearing?

473
00:37:24,943 --> 00:37:26,845
I mean that was
the last time I saw 'em.

474
00:37:26,878 --> 00:37:28,013
He just disappeared.

475
00:37:28,046 --> 00:37:30,449
Oh, you know, we knew
he shot 'em--

476
00:37:30,482 --> 00:37:32,551
Enough!

477
00:37:32,584 --> 00:37:34,886
I do not want
to hear any more.

478
00:37:34,920 --> 00:37:36,154
What?

479
00:37:36,187 --> 00:37:39,057
How cruel, Dean.

480
00:37:42,027 --> 00:37:44,530
And you call that discipline?

481
00:37:53,839 --> 00:37:55,607
What did I say?

482
00:38:15,994 --> 00:38:19,297
* Some day I will drift away *

483
00:38:19,331 --> 00:38:23,902
* Down the rivers 
 and the streams *

484
00:38:23,935 --> 00:38:26,738
* And when I find the ocean *

485
00:38:26,772 --> 00:38:29,608
* I'll be home *

486
00:38:36,281 --> 00:38:38,016
[panther roars in distance]

487
00:38:40,452 --> 00:38:42,854
Did you hear that, boy?

488
00:38:46,625 --> 00:38:48,894
We have nothin'
to worry about.

489
00:38:51,997 --> 00:38:53,999
She can't get us over here.

490
00:38:58,637 --> 00:39:00,572
Cats are afraid of water.

491
00:39:02,240 --> 00:39:04,142
Lily!

492
00:39:16,722 --> 00:39:20,125
I can feed you
anytime I want...

493
00:39:20,158 --> 00:39:23,128
and nobody
would care.

494
00:39:46,251 --> 00:39:47,586
Dear Momma...

495
00:39:47,619 --> 00:39:49,354
I don't want you to worry.

496
00:39:49,387 --> 00:39:51,156
I love you so much.

497
00:39:51,189 --> 00:39:53,625
I am very sorry that I have 
 been a burden lately.

498
00:39:53,659 --> 00:39:56,361
I want to see the ocean.

499
00:39:56,394 --> 00:39:59,064
I want to see 
 what Daddy saw.

500
00:39:59,097 --> 00:40:02,333
I just want to be close 
 to my Daddy now,

501
00:40:02,367 --> 00:40:05,170
and I'm for sure that 
 nothing can hurt me there.

502
00:40:05,203 --> 00:40:07,806
Hurt me there?

503
00:40:12,878 --> 00:40:14,980
I am glad 
 to see you so happy,

504
00:40:15,013 --> 00:40:17,616
but I think 
 it's better this way.

505
00:40:20,151 --> 00:40:22,554
I will send you...

506
00:40:22,588 --> 00:40:24,690
a postcard soon.

507
00:40:26,458 --> 00:40:28,059
Promise.

508
00:40:28,093 --> 00:40:29,861
I love you.

509
00:40:29,895 --> 00:40:31,530
Lily.

510
00:40:36,468 --> 00:40:38,069
She's gone.

511
00:40:38,103 --> 00:40:39,971
We know.
The boat's missin'.

512
00:40:40,005 --> 00:40:42,641
I mean...she's gone.

513
00:40:42,674 --> 00:40:45,276
She's...she's run away.

514
00:40:45,310 --> 00:40:47,278
You don't really think
that she would try

515
00:40:47,312 --> 00:40:49,214
to get to the ocean, do you?

516
00:40:49,247 --> 00:40:51,116
I mean, can she do that?

517
00:40:51,149 --> 00:40:52,117
What does she mean,

518
00:40:52,150 --> 00:40:53,752
'no one will hurt her there?'

519
00:40:53,785 --> 00:40:56,121
Hurt her?
Daddy?

520
00:40:56,154 --> 00:40:58,990
I would never hurt her...

521
00:40:59,024 --> 00:41:02,861
and I would never let
anybody else hurt her.

522
00:41:02,894 --> 00:41:04,996
Edna, call the sheriff.

523
00:41:06,832 --> 00:41:08,734
I will.
Let's go.

524
00:41:08,767 --> 00:41:10,435
Let's go call him, honey.

525
00:41:13,805 --> 00:41:15,741
I'll call him, I'll call him.

526
00:41:21,412 --> 00:41:23,549
Oh, hurry, 
please, Henry.

527
00:41:23,582 --> 00:41:25,183
Thank you.

528
00:41:28,286 --> 00:41:30,421
Whoa!
What's with the gun?

529
00:41:30,455 --> 00:41:32,924
It's only precautionary.
Are you comin'?

530
00:41:32,958 --> 00:41:35,861
Uh...yeah.

531
00:41:35,894 --> 00:41:37,563
Everything's gonna
be fine, Jenny.

532
00:41:37,596 --> 00:41:38,664
I called Copeland.

533
00:41:38,697 --> 00:41:40,699
He's gonna meet me
at the creek with his boat.

534
00:41:40,732 --> 00:41:42,200
Okay.

535
00:42:44,029 --> 00:42:45,063
C'mon, Sooner.

536
00:42:45,096 --> 00:42:47,265
How long does it take
to set a trap?

537
00:42:47,298 --> 00:42:48,734
How long?

538
00:42:48,767 --> 00:42:50,902
Till I get done.

539
00:43:09,054 --> 00:43:11,556
We are going south.

540
00:43:11,589 --> 00:43:14,159
That's the right direction.

541
00:43:14,192 --> 00:43:16,527
I wonder what time it is?

542
00:43:25,170 --> 00:43:29,007
It's about eight o'clock.

543
00:43:29,040 --> 00:43:30,441
I can do it, Joey.

544
00:43:30,475 --> 00:43:32,543
I can tell time
by the sun.

545
00:43:39,050 --> 00:43:41,653
We better go get some
more water before we go.

546
00:44:17,055 --> 00:44:18,356
Hey, McGee!
There's a snake.

547
00:44:18,389 --> 00:44:20,191
Where? Where?

548
00:44:20,225 --> 00:44:21,860
This'n right here.

549
00:44:21,893 --> 00:44:23,628
Damn it, Adams,
don't you start with me.

550
00:44:23,661 --> 00:44:25,663
This is serious.
A little girl's missing.

551
00:44:25,697 --> 00:44:26,998
I know.

552
00:44:27,032 --> 00:44:29,134
Gosh, why you gotta be
so hard-nosed all the time?

553
00:44:29,167 --> 00:44:30,335
Just messin' with ya.

554
00:44:34,005 --> 00:44:35,673
Wait up, Joey!

555
00:44:36,007 --> 00:44:37,709
Oww!!

556
00:44:41,947 --> 00:44:43,849
Go get the stick.

557
00:45:01,599 --> 00:45:03,434
- Hey.
- Hey.

558
00:45:10,675 --> 00:45:13,144
You hear that panther
growlin' this mornin'?

559
00:45:13,178 --> 00:45:15,046
Yep, sure did.

560
00:45:15,080 --> 00:45:17,115
You know, we gettin'
closer every day.

561
00:45:17,148 --> 00:45:20,085
I hope we git him soon.

562
00:45:20,118 --> 00:45:22,553
His hide would bring
a purdy penny.

563
00:45:22,587 --> 00:45:24,389
It sure would.

564
00:45:24,422 --> 00:45:26,724
But after tonight
we're gonna have to lay off

565
00:45:26,758 --> 00:45:28,493
this trappin' for a while.

566
00:45:28,526 --> 00:45:33,398
I got a bad feelin' that this
sheriff is close to our scent.

567
00:45:34,099 --> 00:45:36,067
Yeah, he probably is.

568
00:45:49,180 --> 00:45:50,715
[panther roars]

569
00:45:50,748 --> 00:45:52,050
Did you hear that?

570
00:45:52,083 --> 00:45:53,351
Sure did.

571
00:45:53,384 --> 00:45:55,320
Sounds like
she's gettin' close.

572
00:45:56,988 --> 00:45:58,356
C'mon.

573
00:46:01,759 --> 00:46:04,329
This is where she went in.

574
00:46:04,362 --> 00:46:06,464
She probably didn't use
the motor at first.

575
00:46:06,497 --> 00:46:08,366
It's pretty shallow up here.

576
00:46:08,399 --> 00:46:11,002
Yeah, she doesn't have
a lot of gasoline.

577
00:46:11,036 --> 00:46:12,637
I figure she'll wait
'til she hits the river

578
00:46:12,670 --> 00:46:13,939
to use the motor.

579
00:46:13,972 --> 00:46:15,673
When do you think
she hit the river?

580
00:46:15,706 --> 00:46:17,508
Knowing Lily, I'd say
early this mornin'.

581
00:46:17,542 --> 00:46:19,277
She's quick and she knows
her way around the water.

582
00:46:19,310 --> 00:46:20,879
She got a big jump on us.

583
00:46:20,912 --> 00:46:22,747
Just tell me what you
want me to do, Thomas.

584
00:46:22,780 --> 00:46:24,449
That little girl is
special to all of us.

585
00:46:24,482 --> 00:46:25,716
Thanks, Reverend.

586
00:46:25,750 --> 00:46:27,252
We're gonna need
everyone on this -

587
00:46:27,285 --> 00:46:29,354
especially the good Lord.

588
00:46:29,387 --> 00:46:31,522
Would you do me a favor
and keep an eye on Edna?

589
00:46:31,556 --> 00:46:33,224
I don't want her here
worrying by herself.

590
00:46:33,258 --> 00:46:35,861
All right, but you call us
as soon as you find her.

591
00:46:35,894 --> 00:46:38,329
Now, before we set out
on this important mission,

592
00:46:38,363 --> 00:46:40,631
could we all say a prayer?

593
00:46:40,665 --> 00:46:42,500
Bow your heads, please.

594
00:46:44,035 --> 00:46:46,671
Thank you, Lord,
for being with Lily today.

595
00:46:46,704 --> 00:46:48,840
Thank you for being with us.

596
00:46:48,874 --> 00:46:51,409
Bless the Strickland family
for the safe return

597
00:46:51,442 --> 00:46:53,478
of their grandchild.

598
00:46:53,511 --> 00:46:55,613
Cradle her in your safe arms

599
00:46:55,646 --> 00:46:58,516
so Jenny can cradle
her again in hers.

600
00:46:58,549 --> 00:47:00,952
Guide us swiftly and directly.

601
00:47:00,986 --> 00:47:02,720
In Jesus' Name.

602
00:47:02,753 --> 00:47:04,289
Amen.

603
00:47:05,023 --> 00:47:07,092
All right, Adams,
take some of these men,

604
00:47:07,125 --> 00:47:09,660
get a couple dogs,
cover that side of the creek.

605
00:47:09,694 --> 00:47:13,198
McGee, you get some men,
you scout this side.

606
00:47:19,871 --> 00:47:22,140
I'm going up to the
house to check on Edna.

607
00:47:22,173 --> 00:47:24,375
Jenny, she'll be all right.
Have faith.

608
00:47:24,409 --> 00:47:26,377
Thank you, Reverend.

609
00:47:33,018 --> 00:47:35,520
Sheriff, Copeland!
You better come quick!

610
00:47:37,122 --> 00:47:39,024
What you got, Tim?

611
00:47:39,857 --> 00:47:41,692
Oh, Lord.

612
00:47:41,726 --> 00:47:44,963
These tracks are fresh -
about a half a day old.

613
00:47:44,996 --> 00:47:46,965
Big one, too.

614
00:47:46,998 --> 00:47:48,934
And she's headed downstream.

615
00:47:49,935 --> 00:47:52,770
I can't lose her, too.

616
00:47:52,803 --> 00:47:55,406
I just can't.

617
00:47:57,475 --> 00:48:00,145
She is everything to me.

618
00:48:03,949 --> 00:48:06,217
Oh, baby...

619
00:48:07,785 --> 00:48:10,188
It's okay.
We'll find her.

620
00:48:44,155 --> 00:48:49,927
Well, lookie there what we
done caught in the trap, son!

621
00:48:49,961 --> 00:48:52,998
I guess I done
won that bet.

622
00:48:53,031 --> 00:48:55,066
I guess you did.

623
00:48:55,100 --> 00:48:57,502
Look at that pretty
golden hair.

624
00:49:02,040 --> 00:49:04,242
Look at her leg, Emmit.

625
00:49:04,275 --> 00:49:06,677
She's hurt bad.

626
00:49:06,711 --> 00:49:08,546
What we gonna do with her?

627
00:49:08,579 --> 00:49:10,448
She'll get us in some
real trouble for sure.

628
00:49:10,481 --> 00:49:12,017
You shut up!

629
00:49:12,050 --> 00:49:15,486
Well, now, little girl...

630
00:49:15,520 --> 00:49:18,823
looks like we got ourselves
a real problem here.

631
00:49:18,856 --> 00:49:20,325
Help me.
Please.

632
00:49:20,358 --> 00:49:22,093
No, no.
Now listen up.

633
00:49:22,127 --> 00:49:23,861
I mean, we could let you go,

634
00:49:23,894 --> 00:49:27,432
but then you'd be in
on our little secret.

635
00:49:27,465 --> 00:49:30,801
Now, if you stay with us,
probably come in kinda handy.

636
00:49:30,835 --> 00:49:32,370
And we could learn
you somethin'.

637
00:49:32,403 --> 00:49:35,240
This your rabbit, little girl?

638
00:49:35,273 --> 00:49:37,708
He sure is fat.

639
00:49:39,877 --> 00:49:41,646
Make a good stew, he will.

640
00:49:41,679 --> 00:49:44,015
No!
No, please...he's a pet.

641
00:49:44,049 --> 00:49:46,451
He's not a wild one.
Don't hurt him.

642
00:49:46,484 --> 00:49:48,153
I promise
I won't say anything.

643
00:49:48,186 --> 00:49:49,387
Is that your dog?

644
00:49:49,420 --> 00:49:51,122
Hey, boy.

645
00:49:52,057 --> 00:49:53,958
Aagh, he tried nippin' at me.

646
00:49:53,991 --> 00:49:56,527
Sooner, kill that dog.

647
00:49:56,561 --> 00:49:57,862
- All right.
- Kill 'em!

648
00:49:57,895 --> 00:50:00,131
I guess we're gonna have to
teach you some manners.

649
00:50:00,165 --> 00:50:01,699
No!

650
00:50:01,732 --> 00:50:03,568
[gun fires]

651
00:50:22,387 --> 00:50:24,622
Put the gun down.

652
00:50:32,430 --> 00:50:34,399
You too.

653
00:50:34,432 --> 00:50:37,135
Don't even think about
that knife in your boot.

654
00:50:39,537 --> 00:50:40,905
Now you guys
get out of here.

655
00:50:40,938 --> 00:50:42,707
My rabbit!

656
00:50:42,740 --> 00:50:45,476
Let the rabbit go.

657
00:50:47,345 --> 00:50:48,846
Hey, we just found her here.

658
00:50:48,879 --> 00:50:50,315
We was just tryin'
to help.

659
00:50:50,348 --> 00:50:51,582
Ain't that right, Sooner?

660
00:50:51,616 --> 00:50:52,983
Yeah, sure.

661
00:50:53,017 --> 00:50:54,685
Ya'll just get on
away from here...

662
00:50:54,719 --> 00:50:56,421
before I lose my temper.

663
00:51:00,225 --> 00:51:01,926
Go on!

664
00:51:11,969 --> 00:51:13,571
Okay.
Whoa!

665
00:51:13,604 --> 00:51:15,140
You're hurt pretty bad.

666
00:51:15,173 --> 00:51:17,242
I'm gonna take it off.
It's gonna hurt you.

667
00:51:17,275 --> 00:51:18,543
Hold on.

668
00:51:19,844 --> 00:51:21,379
Okay.

669
00:51:21,412 --> 00:51:22,913
I want you to
stand up for me.

670
00:51:22,947 --> 00:51:24,149
Can you try that?

671
00:51:24,182 --> 00:51:25,783
Come on.
You're a big girl.

672
00:51:25,816 --> 00:51:27,485
You can do it.
Stand up.

673
00:51:27,518 --> 00:51:29,320
Good girl, good girl.

674
00:51:29,354 --> 00:51:30,955
Let's try to walk.

675
00:51:31,789 --> 00:51:33,558
What's your doggie's name?

676
00:51:33,591 --> 00:51:35,526
- Joey.
- C'mon Joey.

677
00:52:03,321 --> 00:52:05,656
We got to get us
some shotgun shells.

678
00:52:05,690 --> 00:52:08,326
And we need us a couple
new guns, too - remember?

679
00:52:08,359 --> 00:52:10,561
Of course I remember, you idiot.

680
00:52:12,062 --> 00:52:14,532
Have you heard anything else
about Lily Strickland?

681
00:52:14,565 --> 00:52:15,966
No, not this afternoon.

682
00:52:16,000 --> 00:52:17,968
All the town men are
out looking for her.

683
00:52:18,002 --> 00:52:20,471
You know the panther was heard
over by their house last night.

684
00:52:20,505 --> 00:52:23,274
Oh, Lord.
What's gonna happen to her?

685
00:52:23,308 --> 00:52:26,577
I can't imagine a little
girl lost in those woods.

686
00:52:26,611 --> 00:52:29,714
I just don't know what else
that family can handle.

687
00:52:29,747 --> 00:52:32,417
They lost a son
a few years ago.

688
00:52:32,450 --> 00:52:35,853
He was a fine boy.
He was in the Navy.

689
00:52:35,886 --> 00:52:39,924
It just took forever
for Jenny to get over that.

690
00:52:39,957 --> 00:52:42,260
What she must
be going through.

691
00:52:42,960 --> 00:52:45,663
You know, those poachers been
settin' up traps everywhere.

692
00:52:45,696 --> 00:52:48,032
That's why that cat
is so close in.

693
00:52:48,065 --> 00:52:50,501
What if she gets
in the trap first?

694
00:52:50,535 --> 00:52:53,304
Well, the panther really
will get to her.

695
00:52:53,338 --> 00:52:56,541
Lordy mercy.
What's this world comin' to?

696
00:52:58,075 --> 00:53:00,778
Well, I've been prayin'
for Jenny and her daughter.

697
00:53:00,811 --> 00:53:03,281
They've had
such a hard life.

698
00:53:06,817 --> 00:53:08,519
I better be goin'.

699
00:53:08,553 --> 00:53:10,688
If y'all hear anything
will you let me know?

700
00:53:10,721 --> 00:53:13,691
Sure thing.
Thanks.

701
00:53:16,627 --> 00:53:18,429
- Howdy.
- How are you boys?

702
00:53:18,463 --> 00:53:20,865
Did I hear you say that
somebody was missin'?

703
00:53:20,898 --> 00:53:22,633
Thomas Strickland's
granddaughter.

704
00:53:22,667 --> 00:53:24,602
- No!
- Yeah.

705
00:53:26,036 --> 00:53:29,006
Well, who all they
got lookin' for her?

706
00:53:29,039 --> 00:53:30,675
The sheriff got
a search party together.

707
00:53:30,708 --> 00:53:32,243
They're meetin' up
down at the mouth

708
00:53:32,277 --> 00:53:35,480
of the river, I think.
You boys wanna help?

709
00:53:35,513 --> 00:53:36,914
Well, sure we do.

710
00:53:36,947 --> 00:53:38,215
- Don't we, Sooner?
- Sure.

711
00:53:38,249 --> 00:53:40,351
I'd hate for anything
to happen to that little girl.

712
00:53:41,018 --> 00:53:44,221
Of course, we're gonna
need a couple of rifles...

713
00:53:44,255 --> 00:53:46,957
Uh, that shotgun and that
one with the scope on it.

714
00:53:46,991 --> 00:53:50,060
Seein's how both our guns
were stolen just today.

715
00:53:50,094 --> 00:53:52,029
- Stolen?!
- Yes, ma'am.

716
00:53:52,062 --> 00:53:53,364
What in the world?

717
00:53:53,398 --> 00:53:54,565
Well, I tell you -

718
00:53:54,599 --> 00:53:56,367
things just aren't safe
anywhere anymore.

719
00:53:56,401 --> 00:53:57,802
That first rifle,

720
00:53:57,835 --> 00:53:59,337
and that shotgun
next to it.

721
00:53:59,370 --> 00:54:00,638
Sure thing.

722
00:54:00,671 --> 00:54:02,507
Thank ya.

723
00:54:03,541 --> 00:54:05,476
What else for you boys?

724
00:54:05,510 --> 00:54:09,079
How 'bout two boxes
of .00 buck for this,

725
00:54:09,113 --> 00:54:11,449
and a 30.06 for that one.

726
00:54:11,482 --> 00:54:12,883
Okay.

727
00:54:13,918 --> 00:54:15,553
Oh, yeah.

728
00:54:15,586 --> 00:54:18,789
I'm sorry, ma'am,
where did you say

729
00:54:18,823 --> 00:54:21,526
that sheriff was meetin' up
with that search party?

730
00:54:21,559 --> 00:54:24,395
I think they'll be meetin' up
at the mouth of the river.

731
00:54:24,962 --> 00:54:26,897
We'll see what we can do.

732
00:54:26,931 --> 00:54:28,699
Yeah, we'll see what we can do.

733
00:54:29,467 --> 00:54:31,502
All right, boys,
we're camping here.

734
00:54:31,536 --> 00:54:32,703
No.
Wait.

735
00:54:32,737 --> 00:54:34,539
We have to keep going.
What if she's hurt?

736
00:54:34,572 --> 00:54:36,273
Lily wouldn't do
anything to jeopardize

737
00:54:36,307 --> 00:54:37,775
that dog or the rabbit.

738
00:54:37,808 --> 00:54:39,777
She knows how to
survive off the land.

739
00:54:39,810 --> 00:54:41,278
She knows how
to stay out of sight.

740
00:54:41,312 --> 00:54:42,980
We ain't gonna find
her tonight, honey.

741
00:54:43,914 --> 00:54:46,417
Do you think she's all right?
I mean, what if she's scared?

742
00:54:46,451 --> 00:54:48,252
Jenny, she's a brave
little girl -

743
00:54:48,285 --> 00:54:49,520
just like you were.

744
00:54:49,554 --> 00:54:51,456
The way her father was.

745
00:54:51,489 --> 00:54:52,857
Come on.
Let's get some rest.

746
00:54:58,496 --> 00:55:00,097
We're camping here?

747
00:55:00,130 --> 00:55:01,999
All night?

748
00:55:22,286 --> 00:55:24,555
[panther roars]

749
00:57:03,220 --> 00:57:04,922
(Sheriff)
Here we are, right here.

750
00:57:04,955 --> 00:57:08,025
I feel that Lily is no
farther than here.

751
00:57:08,058 --> 00:57:10,628
Hopefully, she rested
in this radius right here.

752
00:57:10,661 --> 00:57:13,230
If we spread out, there's no way
we're gonna miss her.

753
00:57:13,598 --> 00:57:16,767
Yeah, but if I know Lily,
she left before sunrise.

754
00:57:16,801 --> 00:57:18,469
She wouldn't let
night cover stop her.

755
00:57:18,503 --> 00:57:20,404
She knows where
she is by the stars.

756
00:57:20,437 --> 00:57:23,107
I'm afraid she got more of
a lead on us than you think.

757
00:57:23,140 --> 00:57:24,775
Yeah, maybe you're right.

758
00:57:24,809 --> 00:57:26,711
But we've got
men and dogs

759
00:57:26,744 --> 00:57:28,713
on both sides
of the creek.

760
00:57:28,746 --> 00:57:31,048
We got ten boats
in the water.

761
00:57:31,081 --> 00:57:33,017
We've radioed the ports...

762
00:57:33,050 --> 00:57:35,352
and it's on the news.

763
00:57:35,385 --> 00:57:36,721
I don't think
there's any way

764
00:57:36,754 --> 00:57:38,889
that we won't find
her sometime today.

765
00:57:38,923 --> 00:57:40,457
Maybe we can put
a stop to all this

766
00:57:40,491 --> 00:57:42,359
crazy behavior
once and for all.

767
00:57:43,193 --> 00:57:45,195
I am about an inch away from--

768
00:57:45,229 --> 00:57:46,597
I don't know what it
is that you think

769
00:57:46,631 --> 00:57:48,098
you're gonna
teach her, Dean.

770
00:57:48,132 --> 00:57:50,367
Well, how about
not to run off?

771
00:57:50,400 --> 00:57:52,436
Maybe she
ran away from you.

772
00:57:52,469 --> 00:57:54,071
You got something
to say about that?

773
00:57:54,104 --> 00:57:56,173
Look, I don't know
what you're saying--

774
00:57:56,206 --> 00:57:58,008
Thomas, he's just
trying to help.

775
00:57:58,042 --> 00:58:00,545
Dean would
never hurt Lily,

776
00:58:00,578 --> 00:58:03,213
and you know that.
You're just tired.

777
00:58:03,247 --> 00:58:04,882
Hey, Sheriff, could I talk
to you a minute?

778
00:58:04,915 --> 00:58:06,250
It's okay.

779
00:58:06,283 --> 00:58:07,685
Y'all excuse me
for a minute.

780
00:58:08,719 --> 00:58:10,387
Thomas.

781
00:58:31,341 --> 00:58:32,843
Well, that's when
we seen her.

782
00:58:32,877 --> 00:58:34,679
That little blond girl
was puttin' up a fuss -

783
00:58:34,712 --> 00:58:36,681
kickin' trying to git
away from that man.

784
00:58:36,714 --> 00:58:38,115
And we went to shoot at him

785
00:58:38,148 --> 00:58:40,417
and that colored
done shot at us first.

786
00:58:40,450 --> 00:58:42,119
What do you mean
he shot first?

787
00:58:42,152 --> 00:58:44,354
He shot at us, told us
not to come no closer.

788
