01:15:38,301 --> 01:15:40,704
God just took
a big paintbrush

1046
01:15:40,737 --> 01:15:43,873
and painted us all
different on the outside.

1047
01:15:45,041 --> 01:15:48,211
I just thought it would
have been watercolors.

1048
01:15:53,016 --> 01:15:55,318
C'mon, Emmit.
It's gettin' dark.

1049
01:15:55,351 --> 01:15:57,353
I don't know what
it is, but somethin'--

1050
01:15:57,386 --> 01:15:59,956
somethin' just
don't feel right.

1051
01:15:59,989 --> 01:16:03,993
You just got the jitters 'cause
of that little Strickland girl.

1052
01:16:04,027 --> 01:16:05,929
We ain't gonna
git caught, son.

1053
01:16:05,962 --> 01:16:08,598
Once the clan catches up
with that dang tugboat,

1054
01:16:08,632 --> 01:16:11,400
that little girl'll be too
scared to tell nobody 'bout us.

1055
01:16:11,434 --> 01:16:13,102
Did you hear that?

1056
01:16:13,136 --> 01:16:14,771
There's somethin' out there.

1057
01:16:14,804 --> 01:16:16,172
Sooner, you're hearin' things.

1058
01:16:16,205 --> 01:16:17,506
Now stop it.

1059
01:16:17,540 --> 01:16:19,776
And don't go shootin' off
that gun neither.

1060
01:16:19,809 --> 01:16:21,410
You'll have the whole
search party on us,

1061
01:16:21,444 --> 01:16:23,546
quicker 'an bees
on a hive.

1062
01:16:24,681 --> 01:16:27,183
[panther growling]

1063
01:16:30,754 --> 01:16:33,790
Don't move a muscle, boys.

1064
01:16:33,823 --> 01:16:36,125
She's right there
in front of ya.

1065
01:16:46,569 --> 01:16:47,937
Drop the guns, boys.

1066
01:16:47,971 --> 01:16:49,673
It's all over.
We heard everything.

1067
01:16:51,507 --> 01:16:53,476
We didn't mean
to hurt nobody.

1068
01:16:53,509 --> 01:16:54,844
Would you shut up, idiot?

1069
01:16:54,878 --> 01:16:56,379
Huh?

1070
01:16:56,412 --> 01:16:59,015
Yeah, but you did.

1071
01:16:59,048 --> 01:17:00,650
And now you've got
a whole county

1072
01:17:00,684 --> 01:17:02,385
after an innocent man.

1073
01:17:02,418 --> 01:17:03,687
Let's go.

1074
01:17:07,657 --> 01:17:09,893
You're lucky we were here.

1075
01:17:09,926 --> 01:17:12,095
Y'all would have ended up
as her dinner tonight.

1076
01:17:34,818 --> 01:17:36,853
God's paintbrush.

1077
01:17:40,656 --> 01:17:42,291
Nathan!

1078
01:17:42,325 --> 01:17:43,659
Be still, Lily.

1079
01:17:43,693 --> 01:17:45,194
Look after Lily.

1080
01:17:49,933 --> 01:17:52,702
Amos Jackson.
Stop the boat!

1081
01:17:52,736 --> 01:17:54,270
What do y'all want?

1082
01:17:54,303 --> 01:17:56,272
We know you've got that
little Strickland girl on there.

1083
01:17:56,305 --> 01:17:57,707
Now pull aside!

1084
01:17:59,508 --> 01:18:01,110
I don't know what
you're talkin' about.

1085
01:18:01,144 --> 01:18:02,879
Stop that boat, Amos,

1086
01:18:02,912 --> 01:18:05,114
or we're gonna
count you guilty.

1087
01:18:05,148 --> 01:18:07,516
Guilty of what?

1088
01:18:09,018 --> 01:18:10,787
Look, I gotta make a delivery.

1089
01:18:10,820 --> 01:18:15,224
You want to talk to me,
I'll be in Selma first light.

1090
01:18:15,258 --> 01:18:16,793
We gave you fair warnin'.

1091
01:18:16,826 --> 01:18:18,828
Next time it ain't
gonna be so easy.

1092
01:18:18,862 --> 01:18:20,663
Y'all better find some
business of your own.

1093
01:18:20,696 --> 01:18:22,565
Now the river gets
narrow up ahead.

1094
01:18:22,598 --> 01:18:24,533
You want to talk to me,
like I said -

1095
01:18:24,567 --> 01:18:26,369
I'll be in Selma.

1096
01:18:26,402 --> 01:18:28,104
Now get on outta here.

1097
01:18:28,137 --> 01:18:30,807
You ain't seen the last
of us, Amos Jackson!

1098
01:18:41,550 --> 01:18:43,552
Are you all right, Lily?

1099
01:18:43,586 --> 01:18:45,254
Yeah. Are you?

1100
01:18:45,288 --> 01:18:47,623
Who were those men?

1101
01:18:47,656 --> 01:18:50,293
Those men won't bother
us anymore tonight.

1102
01:18:50,326 --> 01:18:52,328
Those small boats
can't stay in our wake,

1103
01:18:52,361 --> 01:18:54,230
so it's not a problem.

1104
01:18:55,598 --> 01:18:57,566
Why don't you
get some sleep?

1105
01:18:58,201 --> 01:18:59,936
When do you sleep?

1106
01:18:59,969 --> 01:19:02,972
I'll sleep tomorrow.

1107
01:19:03,006 --> 01:19:05,441
Nathan, get some shut eye, okay?

1108
01:19:05,474 --> 01:19:07,310
- You sure, boss?
- I'm sure.

1109
01:19:14,550 --> 01:19:16,452
Good night, Amos.

1110
01:19:16,485 --> 01:19:17,753
I love you.

1111
01:19:21,024 --> 01:19:22,926
I love you too, Lily.

1112
01:19:35,204 --> 01:19:37,173
Jesse, I know Amos is
a good friend of yours,

1113
01:19:37,206 --> 01:19:39,208
but I just gotta find
my granddaughter.

1114
01:19:39,242 --> 01:19:41,210
I don't know if I should
tell you anything.

1115
01:19:41,244 --> 01:19:43,212
I don't know that you
have a choice, Jesse.

1116
01:19:43,246 --> 01:19:45,681
You see that
woman over there?

1117
01:19:45,714 --> 01:19:47,350
She's terrified.

1118
01:19:47,383 --> 01:19:49,618
She doesn't know
Amos Jackson like we do.

1119
01:19:49,652 --> 01:19:51,220
She doesn't know
what he wants

1120
01:19:51,254 --> 01:19:53,122
with her little girl, either.

1121
01:19:53,156 --> 01:19:55,024
Look, Sheriff, I don't want
no trouble here.

1122
01:19:55,058 --> 01:19:56,826
That little girl's been abused.

1123
01:19:56,860 --> 01:19:58,127
What do you mean?

1124
01:19:58,161 --> 01:20:00,163
Amos found her in a trap
over in the forest.

1125
01:20:00,196 --> 01:20:02,031
He saved her life.

1126
01:20:03,499 --> 01:20:05,301
Why didn't he
bring her home?

1127
01:20:05,334 --> 01:20:07,370
Somebody beat her.

1128
01:20:07,403 --> 01:20:09,172
That little girl ain't
never had a spankin',

1129
01:20:09,205 --> 01:20:10,874
much less a beatin'!

1130
01:20:11,274 --> 01:20:14,377
Jenny, here's your coffee.

1131
01:20:16,179 --> 01:20:18,281
You all right, Thomas?

1132
01:20:18,314 --> 01:20:19,382
You son of a--

1133
01:20:19,415 --> 01:20:21,617
What!
Thomas, don't!

1134
01:20:21,650 --> 01:20:23,152
Get up.
Get up and hit a man.

1135
01:20:23,186 --> 01:20:25,154
You good for nothin'--

1136
01:20:25,188 --> 01:20:27,290
A man?
You sucker-punched me.

1137
01:20:27,323 --> 01:20:29,325
Thomas!
What has gotten into you?

1138
01:20:29,358 --> 01:20:30,793
Ask him!

1139
01:20:30,826 --> 01:20:32,128
He knows what
I'm talkin' about.

1140
01:20:32,161 --> 01:20:33,162
What?!

1141
01:20:34,263 --> 01:20:34,998
How could you hurt her?
What did she ever do to you?

1142
01:20:35,031 --> 01:20:36,599
It was him.

1143
01:20:36,632 --> 01:20:38,401
He beat her, and she
never said a word!

1144
01:20:38,434 --> 01:20:40,169
What are you talkin'--

1145
01:20:40,203 --> 01:20:41,837
Dean, what is he
talkin' about?

1146
01:20:41,871 --> 01:20:43,072
He's a crazy old man.

1147
01:20:43,106 --> 01:20:44,440
Dean?

1148
01:20:44,840 --> 01:20:46,943
Lily?

1149
01:20:57,186 --> 01:20:59,088
No one
can hurt her.

1150
01:21:01,324 --> 01:21:03,326
Oh, my God...

1151
01:21:06,795 --> 01:21:09,232
What did you
do to her?

1152
01:21:09,265 --> 01:21:10,599
What?

1153
01:21:12,735 --> 01:21:14,537
You bastard!

1154
01:21:14,570 --> 01:21:16,305
What did you
do to my child?!

1155
01:21:16,339 --> 01:21:18,241
I didn't hurt her!

1156
01:21:18,274 --> 01:21:20,209
I taught her
how to behave!

1157
01:21:20,243 --> 01:21:23,179
I did it for her,
for you, for us.

1158
01:21:27,650 --> 01:21:29,652
For us?

1159
01:21:31,887 --> 01:21:34,290
I loved you.

1160
01:21:34,323 --> 01:21:36,259
I loved you blind.

1161
01:21:36,292 --> 01:21:37,826
I love you, too.

1162
01:21:39,028 --> 01:21:41,097
What did she
ever do to you?!

1163
01:21:41,130 --> 01:21:43,232
No, no!
Listen to me!

1164
01:21:43,266 --> 01:21:45,901
She was just a little girl!

1165
01:21:45,935 --> 01:21:48,504
Just a little girl!

1166
01:21:48,837 --> 01:21:51,540
She was just a little girl...

1167
01:21:58,314 --> 01:22:00,616
- I love you, Jenny.
- Stay away from me.

1168
01:22:00,649 --> 01:22:02,818
Stay away from you?

1169
01:22:02,851 --> 01:22:04,853
I love you.

1170
01:22:04,887 --> 01:22:06,755
I didn't know all of this
was gonna happen.

1171
01:22:06,789 --> 01:22:08,757
I wanted the best for us.

1172
01:22:08,791 --> 01:22:10,426
I wanted to be right.

1173
01:22:10,459 --> 01:22:13,096
I wanted to go
drive in my car.

1174
01:22:13,129 --> 01:22:14,964
You gotta believe me.

1175
01:22:14,998 --> 01:22:16,465
Come on.

1176
01:22:23,039 --> 01:22:26,142
Oh, my God.

1177
01:22:30,746 --> 01:22:34,017
No...

1178
01:23:05,581 --> 01:23:09,618
[police siren sounds]

1179
01:23:22,498 --> 01:23:23,599
Okey dokey.

1180
01:23:23,632 --> 01:23:24,767
What do you got here?

1181
01:23:24,800 --> 01:23:26,202
I don't see the jerky here.

1182
01:23:26,235 --> 01:23:27,970
You got
the beef jerky in here?

1183
01:23:36,679 --> 01:23:39,115
- Amos Jackson?
- Yeah.

1184
01:23:39,148 --> 01:23:41,684
You're under arrest
for kidnapping.

1185
01:23:41,717 --> 01:23:42,785
What?

1186
01:23:42,818 --> 01:23:44,019
No!

1187
01:23:44,053 --> 01:23:45,988
He didn't kidnap me!
He saved my life!

1188
01:23:46,021 --> 01:23:47,456
It's all right, Lily.

1189
01:23:48,091 --> 01:23:49,858
It's all right.

1190
01:23:50,426 --> 01:23:52,361
- What you lookin' at?
- Nothin'.

1191
01:23:52,395 --> 01:23:54,763
Nothin'?

1192
01:23:54,797 --> 01:23:57,032
Well, you like
little white girls,

1193
01:23:57,066 --> 01:23:59,302
don't ya, boy?

1194
01:24:00,903 --> 01:24:02,471
Amos!

1195
01:24:02,905 --> 01:24:04,307
Amos!

1196
01:24:06,575 --> 01:24:07,876
Amos!

1197
01:24:07,910 --> 01:24:09,512
- Nathan, look after Lily.
- Yes, sir.

1198
01:24:09,545 --> 01:24:11,480
- Let go!
- Amos.

1199
01:24:25,994 --> 01:24:28,264
Today marks a
turning point in history.

1200
01:24:28,297 --> 01:24:30,833
The governor has declared
a state of emergency.

1201
01:24:30,866 --> 01:24:33,169
The National Guard
has been called out.

1202
01:24:33,202 --> 01:24:35,438
Everyone is preparing
for the worst.

1203
01:24:35,471 --> 01:24:37,640
Thousands of men,
women and children

1204
01:24:37,673 --> 01:24:40,109
are here to
stand up for freedom.

1205
01:24:48,016 --> 01:24:50,553
I believe this one needs
some medical attention.

1206
01:24:50,586 --> 01:24:52,455
What happened to you?

1207
01:24:55,524 --> 01:24:57,593
She'll take care
of you, sweetie.

1208
01:24:58,327 --> 01:25:00,663
Are you that little girl
that's been missing?

1209
01:25:00,696 --> 01:25:02,231
He didn't kidnap me.

1210
01:25:02,265 --> 01:25:04,667
I ran away from home
and he saved my life.

1211
01:25:04,700 --> 01:25:06,535
I have to get out of here.

1212
01:25:06,569 --> 01:25:08,070
He's my friend.

1213
01:25:08,103 --> 01:25:09,238
He'll be all right.

1214
01:25:09,272 --> 01:25:10,773
Let's look at that ankle.

1215
01:25:15,244 --> 01:25:17,913
Oh, let's get this
cleaned up.

1216
01:25:46,809 --> 01:25:48,311
You stay right here, precious.

1217
01:25:48,344 --> 01:25:49,945
I'll be right back.

1218
01:26:50,339 --> 01:26:52,040
All available 
 officers are needed

1219
01:26:52,074 --> 01:26:54,142
at the corner of Water 
 and Broad - Immediately!

1220
01:27:08,957 --> 01:27:10,225
Amos.

1221
01:27:10,259 --> 01:27:11,860
Amos, wake up!

1222
01:27:13,696 --> 01:27:16,632
Lily, what are you
doin' in here?

1223
01:27:16,665 --> 01:27:19,134
I came to save you
this time, Amos.

1224
01:27:19,167 --> 01:27:20,703
How you gonna do that -

1225
01:27:20,736 --> 01:27:22,405
all them policemen down there?
There's a bunch of 'em.

1226
01:27:22,438 --> 01:27:24,807
- I'll be right back.
- Lily?

1227
01:27:38,954 --> 01:27:43,258
* To everything - 
 turn, turn, turn *

1228
01:27:43,292 --> 01:27:48,130
* There is a season - 
 turn, turn, turn *

1229
01:27:48,163 --> 01:27:55,237
* And a time to every 
 purpose under heaven *

1230
01:27:55,270 --> 01:27:57,306
* A time to build up *

1231
01:27:57,340 --> 01:27:59,708
* A time to break down *

1232
01:27:59,742 --> 01:28:01,610
* A time to dance *

1233
01:28:01,644 --> 01:28:04,713
* A time to mourn *

1234
01:28:04,747 --> 01:28:08,016
* A time to cast 
 away stones *

1235
01:28:08,050 --> 01:28:15,724
* A time to gather 
 stones together *

1236
01:28:15,758 --> 01:28:20,863
* To everything - 
 turn, turn, turn *

1237
01:28:20,896 --> 01:28:23,098
* There is a season...  *

1238
01:28:23,666 --> 01:28:25,734
Well, my goodness.

1239
01:28:25,768 --> 01:28:27,235
Watercolors, Amos.

1240
01:28:27,269 --> 01:28:29,638
Look at you.
What you doin'?

1241
01:28:32,875 --> 01:28:35,444
* A time to gain *

1242
01:28:35,478 --> 01:28:37,446
* A time to lose *

1243
01:28:37,480 --> 01:28:39,382
* A time to rend *

1244
01:28:39,415 --> 01:28:41,717
* A time to sow *

1245
01:28:41,750 --> 01:28:43,318
* A time for love *

1246
01:28:43,352 --> 01:28:45,354
* A time for hate *

1247
01:28:45,388 --> 01:28:47,890
* A time for peace *

1248
01:28:47,923 --> 01:28:52,595
* I swear it's not too late *

1249
01:29:22,658 --> 01:29:25,293
Now, Lily, you promised
me you'd call your Momma

1250
01:29:25,327 --> 01:29:28,263
and tell her where you was
and how you was doin'.

1251
01:29:28,296 --> 01:29:31,066
I'll keep my promise
if you keep your promise.

1252
01:29:31,099 --> 01:29:32,501
C'mon.

1253
01:29:32,535 --> 01:29:34,069
Okay.

1254
01:29:50,152 --> 01:29:52,555
[phone rings]

1255
01:29:54,056 --> 01:29:57,460
Hello...
Hello?

1256
01:29:57,493 --> 01:29:59,562
Grandma, it's me, Lily.

1257
01:29:59,595 --> 01:30:02,097
Lily!
Lily, honey!

1258
01:30:02,130 --> 01:30:04,533
Where are you?
Are you all right?

1259
01:30:04,567 --> 01:30:06,735
It's Lily.
She's all right.

1260
01:30:09,538 --> 01:30:13,375
You were very brave for tellin'
us the truth about Lily.

1261
01:30:13,408 --> 01:30:15,444
You saved so many
people's lives.

1262
01:30:15,478 --> 01:30:17,480
I'm just so proud of you.

1263
01:30:17,513 --> 01:30:19,815
Lily, I need to talk to you.

1264
01:30:19,848 --> 01:30:22,217
You don't have
to be afraid anymore.

1265
01:30:22,250 --> 01:30:23,519
Dean's gone.

1266
01:30:23,552 --> 01:30:25,153
He can't hurt you
anymore, Lily.

1267
01:30:25,187 --> 01:30:26,822
What do you mean
Dean's gone?

1268
01:30:26,855 --> 01:30:28,290
Where is he?

1269
01:30:28,323 --> 01:30:30,993
He's locked up where he can
never hurt anybody again.

1270
01:30:31,026 --> 01:30:32,495
Lily, I am so sorry.

1271
01:30:32,528 --> 01:30:33,829
Where's Momma?

1272
01:30:33,862 --> 01:30:34,830
Your Momma's
been everywhere.

1273
01:30:34,863 --> 01:30:36,231
She's in Selma right now.

1274
01:30:36,264 --> 01:30:38,366
Momma's in Selma?

1275
01:30:38,400 --> 01:30:39,668
I'll find her.

1276
01:30:39,702 --> 01:30:40,936
I love you, Grandma.

1277
01:30:43,606 --> 01:30:47,710
It's over...
it's finally over.

1278
01:30:54,717 --> 01:30:56,685
Are you all right?

1279
01:31:12,735 --> 01:31:14,136
Momma?

1280
01:31:24,613 --> 01:31:25,814
Momma!

1281
01:31:28,450 --> 01:31:29,685
Momma!

1282
01:31:29,718 --> 01:31:31,153
Lily!

1283
01:31:48,303 --> 01:31:50,305
I'm so sorry, baby.

1284
01:31:52,641 --> 01:31:54,276
Grandpa!

1285
01:32:05,353 --> 01:32:07,556
Thank you, Mr. Jackson.

1286
01:32:07,590 --> 01:32:08,824
You're welcome.

1287
01:32:08,857 --> 01:32:10,626
She's a very good girl.

1288
01:32:26,008 --> 01:32:28,611
I want to thank you
for saving Lily's life.

1289
01:32:28,644 --> 01:32:31,046
No, Thomas.
This time...

1290
01:32:31,079 --> 01:32:32,881
she saved mine.

1291
01:32:41,356 --> 01:32:43,626
- God bless you.
- Thank you, sir.

1292
01:32:48,396 --> 01:32:50,498
Maybe we can get
some fishin' in.

1293
01:32:50,532 --> 01:32:52,134
I think it's a good idea.

1294
01:32:52,167 --> 01:32:54,102
Thank you.

1295
01:32:54,136 --> 01:32:55,638
Sheriff.

1296
01:32:55,671 --> 01:32:57,673
Amos, sorry about
all the trouble.

1297
01:32:57,706 --> 01:32:59,307
Well, we'll work it out.

1298
01:32:59,341 --> 01:33:01,209
Sometimes we have problems.

1299
01:33:53,896 --> 01:33:56,364
I love you, Lily.

1300
01:35:23,018 --> 01:35:26,154
[seagulls in distance]

1301
01:36:17,705 --> 01:36:19,741
Amos...

1302
01:36:24,980 --> 01:36:27,649
I want to thank you -

1303
01:36:27,682 --> 01:36:29,051
for all the things
you've done,

1304
